  <brief_title>Acupuncture to Prevent Postoperative Bowel Paralysis (Paralytic Ileus)</brief_title>
  <official_title>Acupuncture to Prevent Postoperative Paralytic Ileus</official_title>
  <sponsors>
    <lead_sponsor>
      <agency>National Center for Complementary and Integrative Health (NCCIH)</agency>
      <agency_class>NIH</agency_class>
    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>National Center for Complementary and Integrative Health (NCCIH)</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to determine if acupuncture is effective in preventing prolonged
      postoperative paralysis of the gastrointestinal tract among patients undergoing
      colostomy/ileostomy closure.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
